  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ad6b61d5f28e4af49bf9783d096fb8e5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 5Description
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ObjectData
  displayName: 
  lines:
  - 'On April 27, 2015, during the fourth game''s production, the numbers 8 and 7
    could be seen within the code and info on Scott Cawthon''s website, possibly
    hinting at the Bite of ''87.

    One of Foxy''s eyes in FNaF 4''s teasers contain
    an "87," implying he did the Bite of ''87.

    Some fans have even managed
    to translate this into coordinates, pointing to a Virginian pizzeria. This stirred
    up the fanbase to assume this was connected to the game series. This led to the
    pizzeria being heavily harassed by phone calls, but Scott responded with a Reddit
    post, dismissing it as a mere coincidence and discouraging fans from calling
    any phone numbers they may think are associated with the game. He has since removed
    the numbers from the site to prevent further harassment to the pizzeria.'
  nextNode: {fileID: 0}
